    <div class="events" style="padding-top: 60px;">
    <h1>How the Itinerarys are Made?</h1>

    <p>
        Given your input, out website will look around the location of your choosen theater and generate an itenary with things around the surrounding area.
        
        <br>
        <br>
    

        The API we will be using is a NYC gov API that will find events in the NYC area given 
        some of the following parameters having to do with time and location. (The ones bolded are going to be required)

        <ul>
            <li><strong>Start Date</strong></li>
            <li>Borough</li>
            <li><strong>Zip Code</strong></li>
        </ul>

        Not all of these parameters are necessary but they will aid in creating a 
        more timely organized itenary.


        <h3>Simple Demo of how Events will be generated</h3>

        <div class="eventsdemobox active">
            <form action="/submiteventdemo" method="POST" class="eventsdemo" id="eventdemo">
                <input id="sdate" type="date" name="sdate" placeholder="Start Date" class="input" required>
                <input id="borough" list="boroughs" name="borough" placeholder="Borough" class="input" required>
                <datalist id="boroughs">
                    <option>Brooklyn</option>
                    <option>Bronx</option>
                    <option>Manhattan</option>
                    <option>Staten Island</option>
                    <option>Queens</option>
                </datalist>
                <input id="zipcode" type="number" maxlength="5" name="zipcode" placeholder="Zip Code" class="input" required>
                <input type="submit" value="Submit" class="eventssub">
            </form>
        </div>

        <div class="eventsdiv1">
            <div class="eventsdiv2 event1"></div>
            <div class="eventsdiv2 event2"></div>
            <div class="eventsdiv2 event3"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="resetbox">
            <form action="/submit-event-retry" method="POST" class="reset">
                <input type="submit" value="Reset" class="resetbtn">
            </form>

        </div>


    </p>


    </div>

    <div style="height: 40px; margin-bottom: 20px; width: 100%;"> </div>


